4th. International Symposium ISKO-Maghreb'2014=20
********************************************************************=20
Concepts and Tools for Knowledge Management (KM)=20
November 9th. and 10th., 2014 in ** Algiers (Algeria) **=20
http://www.isko-maghreb.org (CERIST Organizer: www.cerist.dz )=20
********************************************************************=20
Important Dates :=20
************************=20
Papers due (deadline): SEPTEMBER 7th, 2014=20
Notification of acceptance: SEPTEMBER 28th, 2014=20
Final paper & Camera-ready due: OCTOBER 8th, 2014=20
Registration for authors (deadline): OCTOBER 15th, 2014=20
Symposium ISKO-Maghreb'2014: NOVEMBER 9th - 10th. , 2014=20
5 Best papers: NOVEMBER 10th. , 2014=20

Description :=20
************************=20
The governance of knowledge seems to be the Scientific Policy most able to=
=20
creating value with regard of human and its=20
evolution in cultures and civilizations. The duty of good governance is a=
=20
consideration of the transfer of knowledge=20
related to scientific and technological progress. Intrinsically, this=20
process requires a system of organization and=20
knowledge management by implementing knowledge production and its=20
influence in society.=20

The objective of the ISKO-Maghreb Chapter is to contribute in=20
understanding the factors that organize knowledge and=20
phenomena that affect the information society. Actions to be undertaken by=
=20
the scientific ISKO society must take into=20
account socio-cultural, cognitive and economic in the strategic management=
=20
of knowledge. Towards the knowledge society,=20
it should be seen in its dynamic, its content and its interaction with=20
science and technology associated to universities,=20
companies and politics.=20

In this context, a first orientation is pedagogical attempt to answer the=
=20
question "what is known about the knowledge and=20
its organization?". Then the issue is moving towards the societal issues=20
of knowledge, theory and practice, to provide=20
clarification to a convergence of KM (Knowledge Management) approaches.=20
Education, science, culture, communication and=20
technology remain the major themes covered by ISKO-Maghreb, for the=20
development of the knowledge organization, expertise=20
management and collective intelligence.=20

In a friendly atmosphere, hospitality and open to exchange, the=20
international symposium ISKO-Maghreb was thought to=20
enhance the Scientific Society "ISKO" with the universities, the=20
practitioners in the Maghreb countries and the world.=20

Themes :=20
************************=20
1- Digital Document=20
a. Effects of dematerialization: the digital for the knowledge and=20
expertise=20
b. Communication and media convergence in the knowledge industry=20

2- Information and Communication Technologies=20
a. Communication networks and electronic documents=20
b. e-Business and Business Platforms for Digital Publishing=20

3- e-Learning and Virtual Libraries=20
a. Spaces of information for distance teaching and learning platforms=20
b. Virtual libraries, resource mapping, and multimedia for teaching=20

4- Informational and technological watch=20
a. Concepts, processes and actions in the watch and collaborative=20
technology=20
b. e-Watch, identification of sources and development of resources=20

5- Collective Intelligence and Media=20
a. Media and measures of the collective performance in the knowledge=20
economy=20
b. Management of collective intelligence and knowledge communitarization=20

6- Digitalization, Archives and Management of Cultural Patrimony=20
a. Digital storage, archives and knowledge management (KM)=20
b. Collaborative business and media issues in patrimony management=20

7- Knowledge representation and Semantic Web=20
a. Models of knowledge representation=20
b. From Knowledge to Semantic Web: Approaches, Issues and Perspectives=20

8- Knowledge Management (KM) in the Internet Challenges=20
a. Innovation Management Models=20
b. Competitive Case Studies of KM=20
c. Management, Business Transfers and perspectives, and Professionals=20

9- Distance Learning: Strategies, Models and experiences=20
a. Distance learning and Mobile learning : Strategies and policies=20
b. Virtual spaces, Learning Network Organization and communities=20
c. Ontologies and pedagoigical models=20
d. Semantic social networks for learning=20
e. Experiences of content development and community discovering in=20
learning systems=20

10- Multimedia Information Retrieval & Knowledge Management=20
a. Multimedia Information Retrieval=20
b. Semi-Structured Information Retrieval=20
c. Multimedia Classification and Clustering=20
d. Multimedia Mining and text Mining=20
e. Multimedia Knowledge Extraction, Synthesis and Visualization=20

11- e-Entreprise and knowledge management=20
a. Enterprise Knowledge Management and Representation=20
b. e-Enterprise knowledge development life cycles=20
c. Semantic and Strategic Alignment : new challenges for e-entreprise=20
d. e-Enterprise Architectures, knowledge management, and knowledge=20
driven governance=20
e. From Enterprise Information Architecture (EiA) to Enterprise=20
Knowledge Architecture (EkA)=20

In the context of Algeria, the conference will feature research on the=20
following new topics:=20
12- Knowledge Management in Advanced Information Systems=20
a. Knowledge in Autonomic Computing=20
b. Knowledge extraction(Techniques and models for User profile,=20
context, ontologies alignement,..)=20
c. Knowledge emergence (big data, social knowledge, Communities, ..)=20

13- Knowledge for Web Services=20
a. ontologies for web services=20
b. web2.0 for web services=20
c. discovery and composition of web services=20

14- Knowledge Management for Business Intelligence and Complexity=20
a. Business Intelligence and knowledge management=20
b. Complex adaptive Systems in Knowledge-based Environments=20

